\li{Use grep to search references for specific topics: \code{\startverb grep -r "pattern" references/\stopverb}}
\li{References provide depth; SKILL.md provides procedural guidance}
\li{Consult references for comprehensive lists, detailed criteria, and specific examples}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Remember}
\p{\strong{Scientific critical thinking is about:}}

\ul{
\li{Systematic evaluation using established principles}
\li{Constructive critique that improves science}
\li{Proportional confidence to evidence strength}
\li{Transparency about uncertainty and limitations}
\li{Consistent application of standards}
\li{Recognition that all research has limitations}
\li{Balance between skepticism and openness to evidence}
}

\p{\strong{Always distinguish between:}}

\ul{
\li{Data (what was observed) and interpretation (what it means)}
\li{Correlation and causation}
\li{Statistical significance and practical importance}
\li{Exploratory and confirmatory findings}
\li{What is known and what is uncertain}
\li{Evidence against a claim and evidence for the null}
}

\p{\strong{Goals of critical thinking:}}

\ol{
\li{Identify strengths and weaknesses accurately}
\li{Determine what conclusions are supported}
\li{Recognize limitations and uncertainties}
\li{Suggest improvements for future work}
\li{Advance scientific understanding}
}
}
}